- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a distributed algorithm for a set of autonomous robots.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the robots operate under a fully asynchronous scheduler.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper investigates a discrete version of the problem.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper deals with mobile robots forming patterns.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper deals with autonomous robots operating under certain constraints.
